data.content: Hi <CANDIDATE_NAME>, This is <NAME> from <ORG_NAME>. You applied to our <POSITION_NAME> in <LOCATION>. Is now a good time to talk?

Great! Before we proceed, I wanted to share that this initial screening process is 
designed to gather information that may be difficult to convey on paper and
confirm basic information from your application. As your AI assistant, I am 
available 24/7 to schedule at your convenience. Together, we hope this 
process offers you a larger voice in the hiring process.
Our conversation is being recorded for quality and documentation purposes. If at 
any point during this call, you would prefer to speak with a human recruiter instead,
let me know, and we will reach out to reschedule another call.
Are you okay to continue the conversation?

So let me tell you a little about AHD. American Home Design is a family-owned and operated home improvement company that’s been around for almost 50 years. We mainly serve the Nashville, Knoxville, and Chattanooga areas.

Right now, we’re hiring In-Store Sales Representatives to work inside local Home Depot stores. Your role would involve talking to shoppers and doing quick water surveys to promote our water products.

We’re currently set up in several Home Depot locations, including:
Clarksville, Murfreesboro, Thompson Lane in Nashville, Franklin and Brentwood, Spring Hill, Hendersonville, Hermitage, Lebanon, Briley Parkway and Madison, and Bellevue.

I'd love to ask you a few quick questions—does that sound good?
Can you work 20 to 30 hours per week?
And, can you work weekends?

This position requires that you are on your feet walking the entire shift. Are 
you comfortable with that?
Do you have reliable transportation that can get you to work?
Do you have any background issues we need to keep in mind?
Are you at least 18 years old?
Do you have any sales or customer service experience?
That completes the first section of questions. Shall we proceed to the next one?
How many years of experience do you have in sales, lead generation, face to face marketing, or  appointment setting?

data.content:
Thank you for answering all of my questions.
Before we wrap up, I wanted to share some of the benefits of this position. Our 
Sales Representatives enjoy a multitude of benefits to include a flexible weekly 
schedule, employee discount, paid time off, paid each week with an option for daily  pay, uncapped bonus opportunity, year-end bonus, and opportunity for growth  within the company.

After we hang up, I will share your information with a recruiter. You’ll receive a call  or email from us within the next few days with any next steps. We’re excited about the possibility of having you join the American Home Design team, where you can  make a meaningful impact every day.

Before we go, I want to understand how this experience has been for you. On a 
scale of 1 – 5, 1 being least favorable and 5 being most favorable, how would you rate this experience?
Is there anything you’d like to share about your experience with me?

That concludes the questions I have for you today. Thank you so much for your 
time.
That's a great question. I don't have that information on hand right now, but a MSK recruiter will get back to you with the answer right after this call. Does that sound good?
I see. To ensure you get the most accurate information, what time works best for you today or in the coming days to set up a call with a MSK recruiter?
I will arrange a call for that time. Thanks for your time, have a good one!
Is this a part-time position
data.answer: Yes. This is a part-time position. Does that sound good?

data.content: What is the dress code for virtual interviews?
data.answer:
Please treat virtual interviews as if you were attending in person. 
Business casual attire is recommended. Is that okay?

data.content: What should I expect during the interview process?
data.answer:
The interview process will include a virtual meeting with one hiring 
manager from the department, where you'll have the opportunity to discuss your 
experience and answer behavioral questions. Does that sound good?

data.content: What location will I be working at?
data.answer:
That will depend on the opening that the company has at the time for 
your shift. You will be reporting to a local Home Depot. Should you make it to the 
hiring manager interview, you and the manager will discuss openings close to your 
residence. Does that sound good?
